1.10
log
@The MirOS project has decided on a new licence template, with working
over hours to redesign the text; some discussion from outside was
greatly appreciated.

We will now not change this template text any more, unless it contains
serious flaws; you might consider this the "MirOS licence 1.0" if you
want (or even file for an OSI certification yourself; we won't do).

All the content in the MirWiki will have to be under this licence
(credits for _this_ idea go to OpenBSD, who placed their PF howto
 under an open licence as well).

ok bsiegert@@
