 * This is a template licence header whose usage is preferred for all
 * files and large chunks of code or other work which have been newly
 * added to MirOS or have been rewritten from scratch. Its use is re-
 * commended in general; it equals the two-clause BSD- or MIT licence
 * but is easier worded, but has the disclaimer more readible (by not
 * being written in CAPS), and within German law scope, its licencing
 * equals a donation; the liability for authors and contributors nar-
 * rows down to damage voluntarily put into the work (for example vi-
 * ruses or evil code; or work which third parties have rights on and
 * did not approve inclusion into the work).
 * In the case of the MirOS project, applicable law is German law and
 * the site of court is designated to be Bonn, Germany.
 *
