1.1
log
@add a template with a licence body to be used for new
code in MirBSD, some application notices and a comparision
to the new template in OpenBSD (which was my idea, from
private mail contact with Theo de Raadt, Message-ID
<Pine.BSO.4.55.0306031758140.10095@@n1.BOFH.bsddeveloper.co.uk> and
Message-ID: <Pine.BSO.4.55.0306031758140.10095@@n1.BOFH.bsddeveloper.co.uk>
References: <200306031745.h53HjdXe026697@@cvs.openbsd.org>)
@
text
@d1 1
a1 15
$MirBSD$

This is a licence template that is preferred to be used
for new code in MirBSD. This is slightly different from
the original UCB licence, but only in wording (should
be equivalent to the two-clause one), and from the one
used in OpenBSD, which looks like a copyleft licence to
me, even if it may be not one.

Please specify the year of the copyright. Additional
years should be separated by a comma, not by ranges.

Don't add extra text to the licence, except if you must.
Be careful about not adding further restrictions.

d5 5
a9 4
 * Everybody who obtained a copy of this work is hereby permitted to,
 * without further restrictions as long as due credit is given to the
 * authors and the notice below is retained, use, distribute, modify,
 * sell, give away, merge or sublicense it.
d18 13
@

